---
import SectionWrapper from '../SectionWrapper.astro';
import Button from '../Button.astro';
import YearInTimeInfographic from '../infographics/YearInTimeInfographic.astro';
import EighteenMonthTrapInfographic from '../infographics/EighteenMonthTrapInfographic.astro';
---
<div class="value-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
<SectionWrapper bg="light" id="services" class="value-section">
  <!-- Section label -->
  <p class="section-label">// 03 VALUE PROPOSITION</p>

  <!-- Intro headline -->
  <h2 class="value-headline">
    <span>One system. Message, site, and tools.</span>
    <span>All connected.</span>
  </h2>

  <!-- Intro comment -->
  <p class="value-comment">// DOES THIS SOUND FAMILIAR?</p>

  <!-- Symptom cards -->
  <div class="symptoms-stack">

    <!-- Symptom 01: MESSAGE PROBLEM -->
    <div class="symptom-card">
      <p class="symptom-label">// SYMPTOM 01: MESSAGE PROBLEM</p>
      <h3 class="symptom-headline">"Prospects find me, but they don't get what I do."</h3>
      <div class="symptom-body">
        <p>Your site describes your process. It doesn't describe their outcome. The people who already know you understand it. Strangers don't. And strangers are the ones you're trying to reach.</p>
        <p>You have three seconds to answer one question: is this the right business for me? Right now, your site isn't answering it.</p>
        <p>We build websites that answer that question before the visitor has to ask it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-block">
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; FIRST IMPRESSION WINDOW:</span>
          <span class="stat-value">50ms</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; LOAD ABANDONMENT:</span>
          <span class="stat-value">53% leave after 3 seconds</span>
        </div>
        <p class="stat-source">// Lindgaard, 2006 · Google, 2016</p>
        <p class="stat-note">// Simple sites ship in under a week.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Symptom 02: TOOL PROBLEM -->
    <div class="symptom-card">
      <p class="symptom-label">// SYMPTOM 02: TOOL PROBLEM</p>
      <h3 class="symptom-headline">"I'm the one holding all the tools together."</h3>
      <div class="symptom-body">
        <p>You didn't plan to become your own IT department. You bought software one at a time, each one solving a specific problem, until you became the glue between all of them.</p>
        <p>The average small business owner juggles four different digital tools every day. Nearly one in three uses five or more. None of them were designed to work together. That's not a software problem. That's a system problem.</p>
        <p>We build apps around how your business actually runs. Not around how a software company thinks it should.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-block">
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; DAILY TOOLS (avg, small business owners):</span>
          <span class="stat-value">4</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; OWNERS USING 5+:</span>
          <span class="stat-value">1 in 3</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; DAILY TIME LOST TO TOOL SWITCHING:</span>
          <span class="stat-value">1.5 hrs/day</span>
        </div>
        <p class="stat-source">// Slack / Salesforce Small Business Productivity Survey, 2024 · n=2,000</p>
        <p class="stat-note">// App projects start at two weeks.</p>
      </div>
      <YearInTimeInfographic />
      <EighteenMonthTrapInfographic />
    </div>

    <!-- Symptom 03: AI PROBLEM -->
    <div class="symptom-card">
      <p class="symptom-label">// SYMPTOM 03: AI PROBLEM</p>
      <h3 class="symptom-headline">"I know I should be using AI. I just don't know where to start."</h3>
      <div class="symptom-body">
        <p>Maybe you've tried it. Maybe it didn't sound like you. Maybe it was one more thing to learn on top of everything else you're already managing.</p>
        <p>Most AI tools are built for everyone. That means they're optimized for no one. They don't know your services, your tone, or how you actually talk to clients.</p>
        <p>The right question isn't "what AI should I use?" It's "what task do I do by hand every week that a machine should handle?" We find that task, build around your data, and train it in your voice. You approve every output before it goes live.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-block">
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; SMALL BUSINESSES USING AI REGULARLY:</span>
          <span class="stat-value">68%</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; AVERAGE TIME SAVED PER WEEK:</span>
          <span class="stat-value">5 hrs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <span class="stat-label">&gt; PROFIT GROWTH LIKELIHOOD (w/ AI):</span>
          <span class="stat-value">+12 pts</span>
        </div>
        <p class="stat-source">// QuickBooks, 2025 · Google, 2025 · U.S. Chamber of Commerce, 2023</p>
        <p class="stat-note">// You approve every output before it goes live.</p>
      </div>    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Routing comment + CTA -->
  <div class="value-cta">
    <p class="routing-comment">// Not sure which one fits? The diagnostic routes you.</p>
    <Button variant="ghost" href="/diagnostic">[RUN THE FREE DIAGNOSTIC &gt;]</Button>
  </div>
</SectionWrapper>

<style>
  /* Amber divider rule at top */
  .value-divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  /* Headline - Geist Sans, two lines */
  .value-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-4);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .value-headline span {
    display: block;
  }

  .value-headline span:first-child {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .value-headline span:last-child {
    color: oklch(0.76 0.18 62 / 0.7);
  }

  /* Intro comment */
  .value-comment {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--text-accent-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  /* Symptoms - vertical stack */
  .symptoms-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  /* Symptom card */
  .symptom-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    position: relative;
  }

  /* Symptom label */
  .symptom-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--step--2);
    color: var(--text-accent-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  /* Symptom quoted headline */
  .symptom-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-pixel);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--amber-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  /* Symptom body */
  .symptom-body {
    max-width: var(--measure-normal);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .symptom-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-accent-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .symptom-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Terminal stat block */
  .stat-block {
    background: var(--crt-black);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-muted);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-feature-settings: 'tnum' 1;
  }

  .stat-line {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-1) 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: var(--step--2);
    color: var(--amber-2);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .stat-value {
    font-size: var(--step--2);
    color: var(--amber-4);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: right;
  }

  .stat-source {
    font-size: var(--step--2);
    color: var(--text-accent-dim);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    padding-top: var(--space-3);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .stat-note {
    font-size: var(--step--2);
    color: var(--text-accent-dim);
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* CTA area */
  .value-cta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .routing-comment {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--step--2);
    color: var(--text-accent-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .value-headline {
      font-size: var(--step-3);
    }

    .symptom-headline {
      font-size: var(--step-1);
    }

    .stat-line {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--space-1);
    }

    .stat-value {
      text-align: left;
    }

    .value-cta {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .value-headline {
      font-size: var(--step-2);
    }
  }
</style>
